					<div id="dsq-comment-body-4959" class="dsq-comment-body">
						<div id="dsq-comment-message-4959" class="dsq-comment-message"><p>Justin, that sounds great.</p>
<p>Many of the hot plates have some fail-safe that triggers if the base gets too hot. That&#8217;s probably why you&#8217;re seeing your temp up to 160-175. Two solutions to the problem are to: 1. get your base out of the pots, or 2. figure out the heat sensing mechanism and disable it.  The Walgreens plate is super easy to take apart plus you get the benefit of controls outside the pot.</p>
<p>Happy smoking!</p>
</div>
