							</cite>
					</div>
					<div id="dsq-comment-body-5282" class="dsq-comment-body">
						<div id="dsq-comment-message-5282" class="dsq-comment-message"><p>Just built my Smoky Pot last week.  I used a diamond blade in a 4&quot; angle grinder to cut a circle through the base of the bottom pot..  It cut easily, and I haven&#039;t had any problems with cracking.  I mounted the lower pot on a frame, and the electric burner is held such that the base is outside the pot but the element is inside.  This allows me to lower the burner and wood pan out of the smoker to add wood.   I also mounted a woven fireplace gasket strip to the lip of the top pot.  This gives a pretty good seal, and it minimized the chances of chipping either pot when removing or replacing the top.</p>
</div>
