					</div>
					<div id="dsq-comment-body-5474" class="dsq-comment-body">
						<div id="dsq-comment-message-5474" class="dsq-comment-message"><p>Most likely your hot plate has an internal heat sensor that turns it<br />off if it gets too hot (which happens when it is entirely in the<br />pots). Most likely you&#039;ll need to open it up and disable the sensor<br />(it is usually mechanical) or separate the base from the burner so the<br />base is outside the pot.</p>
</div>
