						<div id="dsq-comment-message-6054" class="dsq-comment-message"><p>You can use a woven fiberglass gasket for fireplaces as a gasket on your smoker.  I bought mine at Fleet Farm for very little.  Use high temp black silicone as the adhesive.  Don&#039;t use the gasket cement sold right next to the gasket.  I used that first.  It&#039;s too runny, and it didn&#039;t last long.  The regular thick silicone is going strong.</p>
