						<div id="dsq-comment-message-7410" class="dsq-comment-message"><p>I have a 20&#8243; Flower Pot Smoker with a 1,000 watt Walgreens hotplate (modified). It will provide sufficient heat if the temperature outside is 55 degrees or above. Below 55, or with a strong wind blowing, the unit doesn&#8217;t keep the heat at the level needed to produce good Q. I wrap my FPS with bubble foil insulation if it gets too cold outside.</p>
